fields.descriptive_line: Tilly Losch bathroom, designed by Paul Nash, 1930s
fields.bibliography: The bathroom is mentioned in Alan Powers, 'Intimate splendours [bathrooms in grand houses between the two world wars]. 'Country Life', 23 March 2011, vol. ccv, no. 12, pp. 64-67 on p. 66, where he discusses the re-creation of the bathroom at the 'Thirties' exhibition at the Hayward Gallery in 1979, by Julian Feary and Kate Heron. He notes, interestingly that 'it should have found a permanent home'.
